node.text: “Brother I want to tell you that when I seen those beautiful women, my heart soared. If all people seen was there complexion then they are absolute fools. I am dark skinned but what I know is that love and commitment can be found in all shades of black people. I seen two elegant, classy, intelligent looking women in those sisters and if my brother chose them then I knew that there was something amazing about them, I wish it was a real wedding because it meant my brother finally found some Goddesses that could possibly help me to aspire to be something greater than I am. I seen women that I could look up to and that can help me become a stronger person. It may have been just a fashion show wedding but the three of you looked like royalty. The good news is that when you find your Queens and the real ceremony takes place that hopefully my husband and I will be able to attend!!! We love you brother, you are in our hearts! We have our struggles but we see you moving forward and how you refuse to give up so we have to keep moving forward as well.”

Dr.Umar Returns to Brooklyn(NYC): Saturday October 2nd@8am-8pm(must be seated by 10am), “5 Boroughs Black Parent Know Your School Rights BootKamp” Superior Daycare Center, 1741 Broadway, 844-4DR-UMAR, DrUmarJohnson.com, https://www.eventbee.com/v/new-york-city-black-parent-know-your-school-rights-training-bootkamp/event?eid=158095583

Dr.Umar in Yonkers(NY): Sunday October 3rd@9pm(8pm-12am), Total Faith Awards Gala Benefit & Afrikan Diaspora Tribute Awards, “Keynote Address: The Heart of a Volunteer” Grand Roosevelt Ballroom, 2 Hudson Street, totalfaithnetwork.com, 914.920.5957
